Nyandarua governor nominee Francis Kimemia has called for unity, especially in the Mt Kenya counties. He said the regions in the former Central province, Nakuru, Samburu and Laikipia, should unite as one economic bloc.Kimemia (pictured) spoke at Ol Kalou town yesterday, where he thanked residents for nominating him to fly the Jubilee Party flag in Nyandarua. He said nominations winners in the counties need to start thinking about the agenda as an avenue for growth and wealth creation, especially for the Kikuyu community. He said other communities have formed blocs and are raising money to build factories, while in the Central region every county is on its own&rdquo;. &ldquo;We therefore need to unite because no one will come to our aid unless we love ourselves and work together&rdquo;.